.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Source the library, and check if a command exists, then print an ANSI color matrix:
.RS
.nf

#!/usr/bin/env bash

source ./shlib.bash

shlib::header "Check if command exists:   "
if shlib::cmd_exists git; then
    shlib::status_okn "git is installed"
else
    shlib::status_failn "git is NOT installed"
fi
echo

shlib::ansi_color_matrix

.fi
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B SHLIB_VERSION
Set to the library version string after sourcing.
.TP
.B SHLIB_DIR
Set to the directory containing the library file.
.TP
.B SHLIB_LOADED
Set to 1 after the library is sourced.
Prevents double\-sourcing on subsequent
.B source
calls.
